    "Note that unlike the standard SK, which is symmetric around zero, here we must keep track of the signs of the couplings.When µ(N) = 0, we know thatE J [max z G(z)] = O(N 3/2).In the standard SK model, the weights are scaled by N -1/2 to ensure that expected maximum instead grows linearly with N. This is the reasoning for the scaling of the standard SK objective presented in Equation (70).",
